simple%20tips%20to%20help%20improve%20memory%20and%20focus%20while%20preventing%20cognitive%20decline%20that%20comes%20with%20aging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20what%20you%20eat%20can%20significantly%20boost%20your%20brain%20health%20and%20mood%20while%20supporting%20your%20digestive%20system%20all%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20the%20brain%20and%20the%20gut%20are%20closely%20connected%20%E2%80%94%20so%20much%20so%20that%20the%20gut%20is%20a%20key%20producer%20of%20neurotransmitters%20like%20serotonin%20that%20we%20need%20to%20maintain%20mental%20health%20and%20cognitive%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20think%20of%20the%20brain%20as%20an%20above-the-neck%20concept%20that%20is%20unrelated%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20body%2C%20but%20gut%20health%20is%20so%20critically%20important%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Naidoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upshot%20of%20the%20brain-gut%20connection%20is%20that%20eating%20well%20is%20a%20double%20win%20for%20your%20health%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20need%20expensive%20superfoods%20or%20supplements%20to%20do%20it.%20Naidoo's%20favorite%20brain-boosting%20staples%20on%20her%20grocery%20list%20include%20yogurt%2C%20dark%20chocolate%2C%20and%20fresh%20herbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20and%20foremost%20thing%20I%20want%20people%20to%20really%20learn%20from%20this%20class%20is%20that%20healthy%20food%20can%20be%20delicious%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20you%20need%20to%20do%20is%20add%20in%20very%20simple%20ingredients%2C%20easily%20accessible%20ingredients%2C%20whether%20it's%20leafy%20greens%20or%20herbs%20and%20spices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6e5f3dc-754a-477f-8069-02ddfe02b837%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYogurt%20and%20cottage%20cheese%20are%20rich%20in%20protein%20and%20gut-friendly%20probiotics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20major%20staples%20in%20Naidoo's%20fridge%20are%20plain%20yogurt%20and%20cottage%20cheese%2C%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-gut-health-with-food-full-meals-dietitian-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprobiotic%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20packed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffoods-better-than-probiotics-for-gut-health-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeneficial%20bacteria%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20fermentation%20process%2C%20which%20can%20help%20support%20the%20friendly%20microorganisms%20that%20live%20in%20the%20human%20digestive%20system.%20Both%20yogurt%20and%20cottage%20cheese%20are%20good%20protein%20sources%20to%20help%20you%20feel%20full%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20to%20making%20yogurt%20or%20cottage%20cheese%20a%20healthy%20breakfast%20or%20snack%20is%20being%20mindful%20of%20what%20you%20mix%20in.%20A%20lot%20of%20premade%20products%20or%20additives%20like%20granola%20can%20be%20high%20in%20sugar%2C%20too%20much%20of%20which%20is%20linked%20to%20potential%20health%20issues%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0149763418308613%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20risk%20of%20anxiety%20and%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaidoo%20said%20she%20makes%20her%20own%20brain-food%20granola%20(the%20recipe%20is%20included%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fumanaidoomd.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%20book%3C%2Fa%3E)%20with%20hearty%20oats%2C%20seeds%20as%20a%20source%20of%20healthy%20fats%2C%20and%20a%20bit%20of%20honey%20for%20natural%20sweetness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a73bdb4b-87a0-4c94-87db-4a1077a7bbcd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENuts%20and%20berries%20are%20full%20of%20fiber%20for%20a%20healthy%20snack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPopular%20snacks%20like%20chips%20and%20pasties%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprocessed-foods-may-increase-dementia-risk-study-finds-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprocessed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20research%20has%20linked%20to%20worse%20mood%20and%20brain%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaidoo's%20go-to%20snacks%20instead%20include%20nuts%20and%20berries%2C%20which%20provide%20plenty%20of%20fiber%20to%20keep%20your%20digestive%20system%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerries%20are%20often%20recommended%20for%20brain%20health%20as%20part%20of%20eating%20plans%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmind-diet-longevity-brain-health-ways-to-follow-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMIND%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they're%20packed%20with%20disease-fighting%20compounds%20called%20antioxidants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20eat%20antioxidants%20because%20these%20fend%20off%20oxidative%20stress%20in%20the%20body%20and%20the%20brain%2C%26quot%3B%20Naidoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218e612ce-8185-42d9-9238-4ee32956b58e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeafy%20greens%20may%20keep%20your%20brain%20younger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20easy%20way%20to%20eat%20healthier%20is%20to%20add%20a%20few%20servings%20of%20leafy%20green%20veggies%20to%20your%20regular%20meals%2C%20Naidoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProduce%20like%20spinach%20and%20kale%20contain%20high%20amounts%20of%20nutrients%20such%20as%20vitamin%20K%20and%20folate%2C%20and%20research%20suggests%20they're%20linked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmediterranean-mind-diet-linked-to-lower-alzheimers-risk-brain-study-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthier%20aging%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20look%20for%20microgreens%20like%20cress%2C%20arugula%2C%20and%20pea%20shoots.%20These%20are%20easy%20to%20mix%20into%20recipes%20like%20salads%20for%20extra%20vitamins%20and%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20see%20microgreens%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20I%20try%20to%20get%20some%20of%20those%20because%20that%20added%20to%20the%20top%20of%20my%20salad%20just%20is%20more%20nutrition%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Naidoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22793afbe9-cab5-4a2a-abc5-5d22bca410f3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDark%20chocolate%20is%20a%20brain-boosting%20dessert%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBrain%20food%20can%20also%20include%20treats%2C%20according%20to%20Naidoo.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftea-hot-cocoa-good-for-your-brain-according-to-science-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDark%20chocolate%3C%2Fa%3E%20offers%20a%20wealth%20of%20minerals%20and%20a%20specific%20type%20of%20nutrient%20called%20flavanols%2C%20which%20are%20linked%20to%20cognitive%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20only%20is%20it%20a%20brain-healthy%20food%2C%20it's%20low%20in%20sugar.%20So%20rather%20than%20a%20candy%20bar%2C%20I%20have%20my%20patients%20get%20used%20to%20eating%20small%20chunks%20of%20extra%20dark%20natural%20chocolate%2C%26quot%3B%20Naidoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20best%20results%2C%20avoid%20products%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20sugar%20or%20other%20additives%20and%20look%20for%20a%20high%20percentage%20(at%20least%2070%25%20cocoa)%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20your%20chocolate.%20Enjoying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feat-chocolate-cheese-for-better-heart-health-study-suggests-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echocolate%20in%20moderation%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20also%20key%2C%20since%20too%20much%20can%20cause%20you%20to%20overdo%20it%20on%20sugar%20and%2For%20calories%20and%20offset%20the%20potential%20health%20benefits%2C%20research%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaidoo%20added%20that%20pairing%20chocolate%20with%20citrus%2C%20like%20an%20orange%20or%20clementine%2C%20can%20make%20it%20even%20more%20nutritious%20since%20vitamin%20C%20helps%20the%20body%20absorb%20iron.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b19ed97f-a457-479b-bd12-b0100203d627%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFresh