20swelling%2C%20fever%2C%20low%20blood%20pressure%2C%20that%20can%20be%20followed%20by%20necrosis%2C%20breathing%20problems%2C%20organ%20failure%20and%20death.%20People%20over%2050%20are%20more%20prone%20to%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20deaths%20happen%20within%2048%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ken%20Kikuchi%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20infectious%20diseases%20at%20Tokyo%20Women's%20Medical%20University.%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20a%20patient%20notices%20swelling%20in%20the%20foot%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20it%20can%20expand%20to%20the%20knee%20by%20noon%2C%20and%20they%20can%20die%20within%2048%20hours.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20have%20experienced%20recent%20outbreaks.%20In%20late%202022%20at%20least%20five%20European%20nations%20reported%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20an%20increase%20in%20cases%20of%20invasive%20group%20A%20streptococcus%20(iGAS)%20disease%2C%20which%20includes%20STSS.%20The%20WHO%20said%20the%20rise%20in%20cases%20followed%20the%20end%20of%20Covid%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20current%20rate%20of%20infections%2C%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20in%20Japan%20could%20reach%202%2C500%20this%20year%2C%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bterrifying%26quot%3B%20mortality%20rate%20of%2030%25%2C%20Kikuchi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKikuchi%20urged%20people%20to%20maintain%20hand%20hygiene%20and%20to%20treat%20any%20open%20wounds.%20He%20said%20patients%20may%20carry%20GAS%20in%20their%20intestines%2C%20which%20could%20contaminate%20hands%20through%20faeces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718453340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fvhkdvva8_group-a-strep-infection_625x300_15_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frare-fles